  "source_id": "resistant-hypertension",
  "name": "Resistant Hypertension - Vital Signs Query (SBP > 140)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find uncontrolled HTN patients via the PheKB Type-2 criterion: elevated SBP >140 mmHg despite medical therapy. This is the vital-sign-only path — combined with multi-drug regimen, defines Type-2 resistant HTN.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated systolic blood pressure measurements above 140 mmHg, suggesting uncontrolled hypertension.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high blood pressure.",
    "broad": "Find patients with systolic blood pressure (SBP) measurements above 140 mmHg, indicating uncontrolled hypertension despite treatment.",
    "expert": "I need to find patients with uncontrolled blood pressure consistent with the PheKB Type-2 resistant hypertension criterion, which requires documented systolic blood pressure above one hundred forty mmHg. Search Observation resources for systolic blood pressure measurements, coded with the appropriate LOINC vital-signs code, and apply a value filter restricting to values strictly greater than one hundred forty. This vital-sign path alone does not confirm resistant HTN — the full PheKB Type-2 definition also requires concurrent multi-drug antihypertensive therapy — but as an isolated query it identifies the uncontrolled-BP cohort."
  },
